PSI reviewed by parties. Statements made as to sentencing.  
During the statements the defendants mother was removed due to courtroom decorum and outburst.  
AS TO COUNT 1 -   
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 10 YEARS, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 120 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 5 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 5 YEARS.  
Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Earned Release Program. The defendant is not appropriate for the Risk Reduction program.
Court costs and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Complete 400 hours of community service; 
2) No further violations of the law rising to the level of probable cause; 
3) Successfully complete an anger management and domestic violence course;
4) Mental health evaluation and take all prescribed medication; 
5) Attend parenting class while in custody and attend additional course while on extended supervision; 
6) AODA assessment and comply with any treatment;
7) No use or possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia; 
8) Absolute sobriety with random urine screens; 
9) Attend treatment and counseling programs as determined by agent; 
10) No contact with the victim, her mother, or the victim's child (contact with child may be modified to supervised contact if the defendant complies with all conditions of extended supervision and petitions family court and is current with child support); 
11) No contact with children under the age of 16 without consent of DOC - supervised contact with his own children ONLY IF the defendant complies with family court order and the defendant is paying child support and current; 
12) Register and comply with the sex offender registry;
13) Obtain/comply with sex offender treatment; 
14) Seek/maintain fulltime employment (unless SSI prohibits then part time or as determined);
15) Obtain GED/HSED; 
16) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge; 
17) Pay all supervision fees;
18) Restitution will be determined at the next court hearing (bail to be applied first); 
19) Pay applicable costs, surcharges, victim/witness surcharge and assessments; any balance remaining unpaid at that time is to be converted to a civil judgment against the defendant.
Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting and Child sex offender working with children.
